    <script>
        const fullLetter = `My love,\n\nI‚Äôve been thinking about you a lot lately, about how you walked into my life in the most unexpected way and somehow made everything feel lighter. There are days when the world feels loud and heavy, and then there‚Äôs you‚Äîyour laugh, your presence, the calm you bring even when things get messy. I don‚Äôt always say this out loud, but having you in my life is one of the things I‚Äôm most grateful for. You remind me that love doesn‚Äôt have to be perfect to be real. It just has to be honest.\n\nThank you for choosing me every day, even on the days when I‚Äôm not at my best. Thank you for being patient when I‚Äôm moody, tired, or quiet. Thank you for listening to my stories, even the random ones that don‚Äôt always make sense. Thank you for caring about the small details‚Äîhow I‚Äôm feeling, what made me smile, what made my day hard. Those little things might seem simple, but they mean so much to me. They make me feel seen, heard, and understood.\n\nI love how you make ordinary moments feel special. The simple talks, the jokes we share, the times we just sit and exist together‚Äîthose moments are my favorite. They remind me that love isn‚Äôt only about big gestures. It‚Äôs about choosing to show up, choosing to care, choosing to stay kind even when things aren‚Äôt easy. With you, I‚Äôve learned that comfort can be beautiful. I‚Äôve learned that peace can feel like home.\n\nYou inspire me to be better‚Äînot in a pressured way, but in a gentle way.\n\nYou make me want to grow, to be more patient, to be more understanding, to be braver with my feelings. When I doubt myself, you remind me of my worth. When I‚Äôm scared to try, you encourage me to take the step anyway. You don‚Äôt just love me; you believe in me, and that‚Äôs something I hold close to my heart.\n\nI know we‚Äôre both still learning. We‚Äôre learning how to communicate, how to handle misunderstandings, how to be there for each other when life gets tough. There will be days when we don‚Äôt agree, days when we‚Äôre tired, days when emotions run high. But I want you to know that I choose to work through those days with you. I choose patience over pride. I choose honesty over silence. I choose us, not because we‚Äôre perfect, but because we‚Äôre willing to grow together.\n\nIf I ever get quiet, please know it doesn‚Äôt mean I love you any less. Sometimes my heart just needs a moment to breathe. And if you ever feel unsure, I hope you remember this: you matter to me. Your feelings matter to me. Your dreams matter to me. I care about the things that make you excited, the things that worry you, and the things you‚Äôre still figuring out. I want to be someone who supports you, not someone who holds you back.\n\nI admire your strength, even when you don‚Äôt see it in yourself. I admire how you try, how you keep going, how you show up for the people you care about. You don‚Äôt have to be perfect for me to love you. I love you for who you are, for the effort you give, for the heart you carry. And on the days you feel like you‚Äôre not enough, I hope you hear my voice in your mind telling you that you are more than enough.\n\nBeing with you makes me hopeful about the future‚Äînot in a pressured way, but in a gentle, steady way. I imagine more shared laughs, more late-night talks, more quiet moments where everything feels okay because we‚Äôre together. I don‚Äôt know exactly what tomorrow will bring, but I know I want to face it with you by my side, learning, growing, and choosing each other again and again.\n\nThank you for being my safe place. Thank you for being my comfort. Thank you for being my favorite person to talk to when my day has been long. Thank you for reminding me that love can be kind, patient, and real. I promise to keep trying to be someone who listens, who understands, and who shows love not just with words, but with actions.\n\nNo matter how busy life gets, no matter how loud the world becomes, I hope you always remember this: you are important to me. You are valued. You are cared for deeply. I‚Äôm proud of you for who you are and for who you‚Äôre becoming. And I‚Äôm grateful that out of all the people in this world, I get to walk this part of life with you.\n\nWith all my love,\nAlways yours ü§ç`;

        function unlock() {
            if(document.getElementById('pass').value === "10.28.23") {
                document.getElementById('lock').style.display = "none";
                document.getElementById('question-area').style.display = "block";
            } else { alert("Incorrect date, try again my love! ‚ù§Ô∏è"); }
        }

        function moveNo() {
            const btn = document.getElementById('noBtn');
            btn.style.position = "fixed";
            btn.style.left = Math.random() * 80 + "vw";
            btn.style.top = Math.random() * 80 + "vh";
            btn.innerText = ["No", "ü•∫", "üò≠", "üíî", "Think again!"][Math.floor(Math.random() * 5)];
        }

        function showVictory() {
            document.getElementById('question-area').style.display = "none";
            document.getElementById('victory').classList.add('show');
        }

        function startJourney() {
            document.getElementById('victory').classList.remove('show');
            document.getElementById('main-envelope-wrap').style.display = "block";
            startLoveRain();
        }

        function revealMain() {
            document.getElementById('env1').classList.add('open');
            setTimeout(() => {
                document.getElementById('main-envelope-wrap').style.display = "none";
                const box = document.getElementById('main-content');
                box.style.display = "block";
                setTimeout(() => {
                    box.style.opacity = "1";
                    document.getElementById('letter-header').style.opacity = "1";
                    typeWriter(fullLetter, 'typing-container', () => {
                        document.getElementById('reasons-envelope-wrap').style.display = "block";
                    });
                }, 500);
            }, 600);
        }

        function revealReasons() {
            document.getElementById('env2').classList.add('open');
            setTimeout(() => {
                document.getElementById('reasons-envelope-wrap').style.display = "none";
                const box = document.getElementById('reasons-content');
                box.style.display = "block";
                setTimeout(() => box.style.opacity = "1", 50);
                document.getElementById('things-envelope-wrap').style.display = "block";
            }, 600);
        }

        function revealThings() {
            document.getElementById('env3').classList.add('open');
            setTimeout(() => {
                document.getElementById('things-envelope-wrap').style.display = "none";
                const box = document.getElementById('things-content');
                box.style.display = "block";
                setTimeout(() => box.style.opacity = "1", 50);
                document.getElementById('promise-envelope-wrap').style.display = "block";
            }, 600);
        }

        function revealPromise() {
            document.getElementById('env4').classList.add('open');
            setTimeout(() => {
                document.getElementById('promise-envelope-wrap').style.display = "none";
                const box = document.getElementById('promise-content');
                box.style.display = "block";
                setTimeout(() => box.style.opacity = "1", 50);
            }, 600);
        }

        function typeWriter(text, elementId, callback) {
            let i = 0;
            const elem = document.getElementById(elementId);
            function next() {
                if (i < text.length) {
                    elem.innerHTML += text.charAt(i);
                    i++;
                    setTimeout(next, 45); // Slower typing speed
                } else if (callback) callback();
            }
            next();
        }

        function startLoveRain() {
            setInterval(() => { createDrop('I love you'); }, 250);
        }

        function createDrop(txt) {
            const drop = document.createElement('div');
            drop.className = 'rain-drop';
            drop.textContent = txt;
            drop.style.left = Math.random() * 100 + 'vw';
            const duration = Math.random() * 3 + 4;
            drop.style.animationDuration = duration + 's';
            drop.style.fontSize = Math.random() * 10 + 12 + 'px';
            document.body.appendChild(drop);
            setTimeout(() => drop.remove(), duration * 1000);
        }

        function extraLove() {
            for(let i=0; i<30; i++) {
                setTimeout(() => createDrop('‚ù§Ô∏è'), i * 50);
            }
            alert("Sent! I love you so much! ‚ù§Ô∏è");
        }
    </script>
